==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Welterweight
<hw>Wel"ter*weight`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Horse Racing)</fld> <def>A weight of 28 pounds (one of 40 pounds
is called a <stype>heavy welterweight</stype>) sometimes imposed in
addition to weight for age, chiefly in steeplechases and hurdle
races.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A boxer or wrestler whose weight is intermediate
between that of a lightweight and that of a middleweight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weltschmertz</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
